This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the classification of lung nodules using deep convolutional neural networks. It also involves the extraction of handcrafted features, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of support vector machines (SVMs) for classification, which falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
